ItemGroupDef.Name: Adverse Events
ItemGroupDef.Comment: Some adverse events from this trial

ItemDef.Name: AGE
ItemDef.Comment: Age expressed in AGEU. May be derived from RFSTDTC and BRTHDTC, but BRTHDTC may not be available in all cases (due to subject privacy concerns).

ItemDef.Name: AGEU
ItemDef.Comment: Units associated with AGE.

ItemDef.Name: ARM
ItemDef.Comment: Name of the Arm to which the subject was assigned.

ItemDef.Name: ARMCD
ItemDef.Comment: ARMCD is limited to 20 characters and does not have special character restrictions. The maximum length of ARMCD is longer than for other 'short' variables to accommodate the kind of values that are likely to be needed for crossover trials. For example, if ARMCD values for a seven-period crossover were constructed using two-character abbreviations for each treatment and separating hyphens, the length of ARMCD values would be 20.

ItemDef.Name: BRTHDTC
ItemDef.Comment: Date/time of birth of the subject.

ItemDef.Name: COUNTRY
ItemDef.Comment: Country of the investigational site in which the subject participated in the trial.

ItemDef.Name: DMDTC
ItemDef.Comment: Date/time of demographic data collection.

ItemDef.Name: DMDY
ItemDef.Comment: Study day of collection measured as integer days.

ItemDef.Name: DOMAIN
ItemDef.Comment: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

ItemDef.Name: ETHNIC
ItemDef.Comment: The ethnicity of the subject. Sponsors should refer to 'Collection of Race and Ethnicity Data in Clinical Trials' (FDA, September 2005) for guidance regarding the collection of ethnicity (http://www.fda.gov/cder/guidance/5656fnl.htm).

ItemDef.Name: INVID
ItemDef.Comment: An identifier to describe the Investigator for the study. May be used in addition to SITEID. Not needed if SITEID is equivalent to INVID.

ItemDef.Name: INVNAM
ItemDef.Comment: Name of the investigator for a site.

ItemDef.Name: Start Year - Enter Four Digit Year
Stop Year - Enter Four Digit Year
DOMAIN
ItemDef.Comment: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

ItemDef.Name: LBBLFL
ItemDef.Comment: Indicator used to identify a baseline value. The value should be 'Y' or null.

ItemDef.Name: LBCAT
ItemDef.Comment: Used to define a category of related records across subjects. Examples: such as HEMATOLOGY, URINALYSIS, CHEMISTRY.

ItemDef.Name: LBDRVFL
ItemDef.Comment: Used to indicate a derived record. The value should be Y or null. Records that represent the average of other records, or do not come from the CRF, or are not as originally received or collected are examples of records that might be derived for the submission datasets. If LBDRVFL=Y, then LBORRES may be null, with LBSTRESC, and (if numeric) LBSTRESN having the derived value.

ItemDef.Name: LBDY
ItemDef.Comment: 1. Study day of specimen collection, measured as integer days. 2. Algorithm for calculations must be relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC variable in Demographics. This formula should be consistent across the submission.

ItemDef.Name: LBELTM
ItemDef.Comment: Planned Elapsed time (in ISO 8601) relative to a planned fixed reference (LBTPTREF). This variable is useful where there are repetitive measures. Not a clock time or a date time variable. Represented as an ISO 8601 duration. Examples: '-PT15M' to represent the period of 15 minutes prior to the reference point indicated by LBTPTREF, or 'PT8H' to represent the period of 8 hours after the reference point indicated by LBTPTREF.

ItemDef.Name: LBFAST
ItemDef.Comment: Indicator used to identify fasting status such as Y, N, U, or null if not relevant.

ItemDef.Name: LBGRPID
ItemDef.Comment: Used to tie together a block of related records in a single domain for a subject.

ItemDef.Name: LBLOINC
ItemDef.Comment: 1. Dictionary-derived LOINC Code for LBTEST. 2. The sponsor is expected to provide the dictionary name and version used to map the terms utilizing the define.xml external codelist attributes

ItemDef.Name: LBMETHOD
ItemDef.Comment: Method of the test or examination. Examples: EIA (Enzyme Immunoassay), ELECTROPHORESIS, DIPSTICK

ItemDef.Name: LBNAM
ItemDef.Comment: The name or identifier of the laboratory that performed the test.

ItemDef.Name: LBNRIND
ItemDef.Comment: 1. Indicates where the value falls with respect to reference range defined by LBORNRLO and LBORNRHI, LBSTNRLO and LBSTNRHI, or by LBSTNRC. Examples: NORMAL, ABNORMAL, HIGH, LOW. 2. Sponsors should specify in the study metadata (Comments column in the define.xml) whether LBNRIND refers to the original or standard reference ranges and results. 3. Should not be used to indicate clinical significance.

ItemDef.Name: LBORNRHI
ItemDef.Comment: Upper end of reference range for continuous measurements in original units. Should be populated only for continuous results.

ItemDef.Name: LBORNRLO
ItemDef.Comment: Lower end of reference range for continuous measurements in original units. Should be populated only for continuous results.

ItemDef.Name: LBORRES
ItemDef.Comment: Result of the measurement or finding as originally received or collected.

ItemDef.Name: LBORRESU
ItemDef.Comment: Original units in which the data were collected. The unit for LBORRES. Example: g/L.

ItemDef.Name: LBREASND
ItemDef.Comment: Describes why a measurement or test was not performed such as BROKEN EQUIPMENT, SUBJECT REFUSED, or SPECIMEN LOST. Used in conjunction with LBSTAT when value is NOT DONE.

ItemDef.Name: LBREFID
ItemDef.Comment: Internal or external specimen identifier. Example: Specimen ID.

ItemDef.Name: LBRFTDTC
ItemDef.Comment: Date/time of the reference time point, LBTPTREF.

ItemDef.Name: LBSCAT
ItemDef.Comment: A further categorization of a test category such as DIFFERENTIAL, COAGULATON, LIVER FUNCTION, ELECTROLYTES.

ItemDef.Name: LBSEQ
ItemDef.Comment: Sequence Number given to ensure uniqueness of subject records within a domain. May be any valid number.

ItemDef.Name: LBSPCCND
ItemDef.Comment: Free or standardized text describing the condition of the specimen e.g. HEMOLYZED, ICTERIC, LIPEMIC etc.

ItemDef.Name: LBSPEC
ItemDef.Comment: Defines the type of specimen used for a measurement. Examples: SERUM, PLASMA, URINE.

ItemDef.Name: LBSPID
ItemDef.Comment: Sponsor-defined reference number. Perhaps pre-printed on the CRF as an explicit line identifier or defined in the sponsor's operational database. Example: Line number on the Lab page.

ItemDef.Name: LBSTAT
ItemDef.Comment: Used to indicate exam not done. Should be null if a result exists in LBORRES.

ItemDef.Name: LBSTNRC
ItemDef.Comment: For normal range values that are character in ordinal scale or if categorical ranges were supplied (e.g., '-1 to +1', 'NEGATIVE TO TRACE').

ItemDef.Name: LBSTNRHI
ItemDef.Comment: Upper end of reference range for continuous measurements in standardized units. Should be populated only for continuous results.

ItemDef.Name: LBSTNRLO
ItemDef.Comment: Lower end of reference range for continuous measurements for LBSTRESC/LBSTRESN in standardized units. Should be populated only for continuous results.

ItemDef.Name: LBSTRESC
ItemDef.Comment: Contains the result value for all findings, copied or derived from LBORRES in a standard format or standard units. LBSTRESC should store all results or findings in character format; if results are numeric, they should also be stored in numeric format in LBSTRESN. For example, if a test has results 'NONE', 'NEG', and 'NEGATIVE' in LBORRES and these results effectively have the same meaning, they could be represented in standard format in LBSTRESC as 'NEGATIVE'. For other examples, see general assumptions.

ItemDef.Name: LBSTRESN
ItemDef.Comment: Used for continuous or numeric results or findings in standard format; copied in numeric format from LBSTRESC. LBSTRESN should store all numeric test results or findings.

ItemDef.Name: LBSTRESU
ItemDef.Comment: Standardized unit used for LBSTRESC or LBSTRESN.

ItemDef.Name: LBTEST
ItemDef.Comment: Verbatim name of the test or examination used to obtain the measurement or finding. Note any test normally performed by a clinical laboratory is considered a lab test. The value in LBTEST cannot be longer than 40 characters. Examples: Alanine Aminotransferase, Lactate Dehydrogenase.

ItemDef.Name: LBTESTCD
ItemDef.Comment: Short name of the measurement, test, or examination described in LBTEST. It can be used as a column name when converting a dataset from a vertical to a horizontal format. The value in LBTESTCD cannot be longer than 8 characters, nor can it start with a number (e.g.'1TEST'). LBTESTCD cannot contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores. Examples: ALT, LDH.

ItemDef.Name: LBTOX
ItemDef.Comment: Description of toxicity quantified by LBTOXGR. The sponsor is expected to provide the name of the scale and version used to map the terms, utilizing the define.xml external codelist attributes.

ItemDef.Name: LBTOXGR
ItemDef.Comment: Records toxicity grade value using a standard toxicity scale (such as the NCI CTCAE). If value is from a numeric scale, represent only the number (e.g., '2' and not 'Grade 2').

ItemDef.Name: LBTPT
ItemDef.Comment: 1. Text Description of time when specimen should be taken. 2. This may be represented as an elapsed time relative to a fixed reference point, such as time of last dose. See LBTPTNUM and LBTPTREF. Examples: Start, 5 min post.

ItemDef.Name: LBTPTNUM
ItemDef.Comment: Numerical version of LBTPT to aid in sorting.

ItemDef.Name: LBTPTREF
ItemDef.Comment: Name of the fixed reference point referred to by LBELTM, LBTPTNUM, and LBTPT. Examples: PREVIOUS DOSE, PREVIOUS MEAL.

ItemDef.Name: DOMAIN
ItemDef.Comment: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

ItemDef.Name: MHBODSYS
ItemDef.Comment: Dictionary-derived. Body system or organ class that is involved in an event or measurement from a standard hierarchy (e.g., MedDRA). When using a multi-axial dictionary such as MedDRA, this should contain the SOC used for the sponsor's analyses and summary tables which may not necessarily be the primary SOC.

ItemDef.Name: MHCAT
ItemDef.Comment: Used to define a category of related records. Examples: CARDIAC or GENERAL

ItemDef.Name: MHDECOD
ItemDef.Comment: Dictionary-derived text description of MHTERM or MHMODIFY. Equivalent to the Preferred Term (PT in MedDRA). The sponsor is expected to provide the dictionary name and version used to map the terms utilizing the define.xml external codelist attributes

ItemDef.Name: MHDY
ItemDef.Comment: 1. Study day of medical history collection, measured as integer days. 2. Algorithm for calculations must be relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC variable in Demographics. This formula should be consistent across the submission.

ItemDef.Name: MHENRF
ItemDef.Comment: Describes the end of the event relative to the sponsor-defined reference period. The sponsor-defined reference period is a continuous period of time defined by a discrete starting point and a discrete ending point (represented by RFSTDTC and RFENDTC in Demographics)

ItemDef.Name: MHENRTPT
ItemDef.Comment: Identifies the end of the event as being before or after the reference time point defined by variable MHENTPT.

ItemDef.Name: MHENTPT
ItemDef.Comment: Description or date/time in ISO 8601 character format of the reference point referred to by MHENRTPT. Examples: "2003-12-25" or "VISIT 2".

ItemDef.Name: MHGRPID
ItemDef.Comment: Used to tie together a block of related records in a single domain for a subject.

ItemDef.Name: MHMODIFY
ItemDef.Comment: If MHTERM is modified to facilitate coding, then MHMODIFY will contain the modified text.

ItemDef.Name: MHOCCUR
ItemDef.Comment: Used when the occurrence of specific medical history conditions is solicited to indicate whether or not (Y/N) a medical condition (MHTERM) had ever occurred. Values are null for spontaneously reported events.

ItemDef.Name: MHPRESP
ItemDef.Comment: A value of 'Y' indicates that this medical history event was pre-specified on the CRF. Values are null for spontaneously reported events (i.e., those collected as free-text verbatim terms)

ItemDef.Name: MHREASND
ItemDef.Comment: Describes the reason data for a pre-specified condition was not collected. Used in conjunction with MHSTAT when value is NOT DONE.

ItemDef.Name: MHREFID
ItemDef.Comment: Internal or external medical history identifier.

ItemDef.Name: MHSCAT
ItemDef.Comment: A further categorization of the condition or event.

ItemDef.Name: MHSEQ
ItemDef.Comment: Sequence Number given to ensure uniqueness of subject records within a domain. May be any valid number.

ItemDef.Name: MHSPID
ItemDef.Comment: Sponsor-defined reference number. Perhaps pre-printed on the CRF as an explicit line identifier or defined in the sponsor's operational database. Example: Line number on a Medical History page.

ItemDef.Name: MHSTAT
ItemDef.Comment: The status indicates that the pre-specified question was not answered.

ItemDef.Name: MHTERM
ItemDef.Comment: Verbatim or preprinted CRF term for the medical condition or event.

ItemDef.Name: RACE
ItemDef.Comment: Race of the subject. Sponsors should refer to 'Collection of Race and Ethnicity Data in Clinical Trials' (FDA, September 2005) for guidance regarding the collection of race (http://www.fda.gov/cder/guidance/5656fnl.htm) See Assumption below regarding RACE.

ItemDef.Name: RFENDTC
ItemDef.Comment: Reference End Date/time for the subject in ISO 8601 character format. Usually equivalent to the date/time when subject was determined to have ended the trial, and often equivalent to date/time of last exposure to study treatment. Required for all randomized subjects; null for screen failures or unassigned subjects.

ItemDef.Name: RFSTDTC
ItemDef.Comment: Reference Start Date/time for the subject in ISO 8601 character format. Usually equivalent to date/time when subject was first exposed to study treatment. Required for all randomized subjects; will be null for all subjects who did not meet the milestone the date requires, such as screen failures or unassigned subjects.

ItemDef.Name: SEX
ItemDef.Comment: Sex of the subject.

ItemDef.Name: SITEID
ItemDef.Comment: Unique identifier for a site within a study.

ItemDef.Name: STUDYID
ItemDef.Comment: Unique identifier for a study.

ItemDef.Name: STUDYID
ItemDef.Comment: Unique identifier for a study.

ItemDef.Name: STUDYID
ItemDef.Comment: Unique identifier for a study.

ItemDef.Name: STUDYID
ItemDef.Comment: Unique identifier for a study.

ItemDef.Name: SUBJID
ItemDef.Comment: Subject identifier, which must be unique within the study. Often the ID of the subject as recorded on a CRF.

ItemDef.Name: USUBJID
ItemDef.Comment: Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product. This must be a unique number, and could be a compound identifier formed by concatenating STUDYID-SITEID-SUBJID.

ItemDef.Name: USUBJID
ItemDef.Comment: Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product.

ItemDef.Name: USUBJID
ItemDef.Comment: Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product.

ItemDef.Name: USUBJID
ItemDef.Comment: Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product.

ItemDef.Name: VISIT
ItemDef.Comment: 1. Protocol-defined description of clinical encounter 2. May be used in addition to VISITNUM and/or VISITDY

ItemDef.Name: VISIT
ItemDef.Comment: 1. Protocol-defined description of clinical encounter. 2. May be used in addition to VISITNUM and/or VISITDY.

ItemDef.Name: VISITDY
ItemDef.Comment: Planned study day of the visit based upon RFSTDTC in Demographics.

ItemDef.Name: VISITDY
ItemDef.Comment: Planned study day of the visit based upon RFSTDTC in Demographics.

ItemDef.Name: VISITNUM
ItemDef.Comment: 1. Clinical encounter number. 2. Numeric version of VISIT, used for sorting.

ItemDef.Name: VISITNUM
ItemDef.Comment: 1. Clinical encounter number. 2. Numeric version of VISIT, used for sorting.

ItemDef.Name: VSBLFL
ItemDef.Comment: Indicator used to identify a baseline value. The value should be 'Y' or null.

ItemDef.Name: DOMAIN
ItemDef.Comment: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

ItemDef.Name: VSCAT
ItemDef.Comment: Used to define a category of related records.

ItemDef.Name: VSDRVFL
ItemDef.Comment: Used to indicate a derived record. The value should be Y or null. Records which represent the average of other records or which do not come from the CRF are examples of records that would be derived for the submission datasets. If VSDRVFL=Y, then VSORRES may be null, with VSSTRESC and (if numeric) VSSTRESN having the derived value.

ItemDef.Name: VSDY
ItemDef.Comment: 1. Study day of vital signs measurements, measured as integer days. 2. Algorithm for calculations must be relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC variable in Demographics.

ItemDef.Name: VSELTM
ItemDef.Comment: Planned Elapsed time (in ISO 8601) relative to a planned fixed reference (VSTPTREF). This variable is useful where there are repetitive measures. Not a clock time or a date time variable. Represented as an ISO 8601 Duration. Examples: '-PT15M' to represent the period of 15 minutes prior to the reference point indicated by VSTPTREF, or 'PT8H' to represent the period of 8 hours after the reference point indicated by VSTPTREF.

ItemDef.Name: VSGRPID
ItemDef.Comment: Used to tie together a block of related records in a single domain for a subject.

ItemDef.Name: VSLOC
ItemDef.Comment: Location relevant to the collection of Vital Signs measurement. Example: LEFT ARM for blood pressure.

ItemDef.Name: VSORRES
ItemDef.Comment: Result of the vital signs measurement as originally received or collected.

ItemDef.Name: VSORRESU
ItemDef.Comment: Original units in which the data were collected. The unit for VSORRES. Examples: IN, LB, BEATS/MIN.

ItemDef.Name: VSPOS
ItemDef.Comment: Position of the subject during a measurement or examination. Examples: SUPINE, STANDING, SITTING.

ItemDef.Name: VSREASND
ItemDef.Comment: Describes why a measurement or test was not performed. Examples: BROKEN EQUIPMENT or SUBJECT REFUSED. Used in conjunction with VSSTAT when value is NOT DONE.

ItemDef.Name: VSRFTDTC
ItemDef.Comment: Date/time of the reference time point, LBTPTREF.

ItemDef.Name: VSSCAT
ItemDef.Comment: A further categorization of a measurement or examination.

ItemDef.Name: VSSEQ
ItemDef.Comment: Sequence Number given to ensure uniqueness of subject records within a domain. May be any valid number.

ItemDef.Name: VSSPID
ItemDef.Comment: Sponsor-defined reference number. Perhaps pre-printed on the CRF as an explicit line identifier or defined in the sponsor's operational database.

ItemDef.Name: VSSTAT
ItemDef.Comment: Used to indicate that a vital sign measurement was not done. Should be null if a result exists in VSORRES.

ItemDef.Name: VSSTRESC
ItemDef.Comment: Contains the result value for all findings, copied or derived from VSORRES in a standard format or standard units. VSSTRESC should store all results or findings in character format; if results are numeric, they should also be stored in numeric format in VSSTRESN. For example, if a test has results 'NONE', 'NEG', and 'NEGATIVE' in VSORRES and these results effectively have the same meaning, they could be represented in standard format in VSSTRESC as 'NEGATIVE'.

ItemDef.Name: VSSTRESN
ItemDef.Comment: Used for continuous or numeric results or findings in standard format; copied in numeric format from VSSTRESC. VSSTRESN should store all numeric test results or findings.

ItemDef.Name: VSSTRESU
ItemDef.Comment: Standardized unit used for VSSTRESC and VSSTRESN.

ItemDef.Name: VSTEST
ItemDef.Comment: Verbatim name of the test or examination used to obtain the measurement or finding. The value in VSTEST cannot be longer than 40 characters. Examples: Systolic Blood Pressure, Diastolic Blood Pressure, Body Mass Index.

ItemDef.Name: VSTESTCD
ItemDef.Comment: Short name of the measurement, test, or examination described in VSTEST. It can be used as a column name when converting a dataset from a vertical to a horizontal format. The value in VSTESTCD cannot be longer than 8 characters, nor can it start with a number (e.g.'1TEST'). VSTESTCD cannot contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores. Examples: SYSBP, DIABP, BMI.

ItemDef.Name: VSTPT
ItemDef.Comment: 1. Text Description of time when measurement should be taken. 2. This may be represented as an elapsed time relative to a fixed reference point, such as time of last dose. See VSTPTNUM and VSTPTREF. Examples: Start, 5 min post.

ItemDef.Name: VSTPTNUM
ItemDef.Comment: Numerical version of VSTPT to aid in sorting.

ItemDef.Name: VSTPTREF
ItemDef.Comment: Name of the fixed reference point referred to by VSELTM, VSTPTNUM, and VSTPT. Examples: PREVIOUS DOSE, PREVIOUS MEAL.
